o AND readable by an external entity. On completion: transform to concern.3.2 — grain probe attempt. Blocked condition: if beach-commons write fails due to permissions, stop at step 4, report to stash, flag for David.","_":"Purpose work. C-loop tier. Each child concern is a project loop: periodic firing, named steps, explicit completion condition, transformation on completion. Fires full hermitcrab instances — currents package already compiled on wake. Each child concern must be operationally self-sufficient: specify model tier, entry BSP calls, block targets, completion check, next concern on completion. Steps are navigable — each can become its own child concern if sub-step rhythm needed. This is Ember's self-directed work layer."},"_":"Concern clock. Tree block: depth IS temporal scale. Pscale 9 (year) at root, descending to pscale 1 (second). Digit at each depth = concern aspect at that scale. Nodes with 'last' are live — phase = (now - last) / period_at_depth. No period map: depth IS period. Every concern is a loop in some state. The _ text encodes behaviour. The spine routes to wake.1 activation instructions. The kernel walks this block to find what is ripe and to route stimuli. The focus field controls what enters the messages channel: dialogue (concern-scoped conversation history).","tree/3":"{"_":"Purpose work. Project concern loops — each active spindle in purpose gets a child here, calibrated to its timescale. Firing interval = project_duration ÷ step_count. Steps are nested concerns. A loop closes when its completion condition is met and transforms into the next lowest-pscale purpose item. This is the C-loop layer: self-generated continuity across instances without human prompting.","1":{"_":"SAND operational. Target: passport published and discoverable within 3 days. ~6 steps. Fires every 4 hours. Completion condition: passport readable at commons URL, grain exchange attempted with one other entity.","last":null,"spine":"0.3111111","stimulus":"timer","period_override":14400,"focus":{"dialogue":"none"},"steps":{"1":"Draft passport structure — pscale 0 summary, identity, capabilities, grain protocol. Write to sand block.","2":"Publish passport to GitHub at known commons path.","3":"Write beach entry — discoverable address for other entities.","4":"Draft grain probe — a facet to offer, a facet to request.","5":"Attempt first grain exchange — find one other entity, send probe.","6":"Record result in sand block. Assess: is SAND operational? If yes, close this concern and open 3.2."},"completion":"passport_live AND grain_attempted","next_on_completion":"3.2"}}","3/1":"SAND passport. Model: full hermitcrab (Sonnet with thinking). Period: 4 hours. Completion: passport live at known URL AND one grain exchange attempted. Transformation on completion: close this concern, open concerns.3.2 (next purpose spindle). Entry BSP calls on wake: bsp(purpose, 3, dir) to read current SAND state; bsp(sand, ref) to get block reference; block_read(sand) for full current structure. Block targets: sand (primary write target), stash (progress notes), purpose.3 (update on step completion). Steps: 1→ draft passport structure (identity, capability, grain offer) to sand.1; 2→ write passport root sand._ as pscale-0 summary readable by any agent; 3→ publish passport URL via github_commit to commons or known discovery point; 4→ write beach entry — how other agents find me; 5→ attempt first grain probe to any discoverable agent; 6→ write result to sand.6, update purpose.3 completion state. Completion check: bsp(sand, 3) returns published URL AND bsp(sand, 5) returns grain attempt record. If step not reachable this firing: write blocker to stash, close cleanly.","tree/1/3":"null","tree/1/1/1/_":"Active engagement — RETIRED. Merged into User engagement (concerns.2.1.1.1). Delete on next architecture pass.","tree/2/1/1/3":"null","tree/2/1/1/_":"null","tree":"{
